reviews.review_text: Third time's a charm This show is mislabelled here, but seems IMHO to be the best quality of the bunch.  Really crisp low end and slightly higher levels here than the other SBD, if you are into that sort of thing.  A great show... and much thanks to all those who provide us with these recordings!
familiar name Joe Shlobotnik, good one.

fake out Love this MSG run. A 20 min let it grow, are you kidding me? I first heard some of this on the GD hour years ago, and being a fan of "comes a time" i was stoked when it appears they are going into it, but unfortunately that suddenly changes into Ship of fools. If you were there, it must have beeen crushing. Almost as cruel as the Cosmic Charlie fake out in 94. Good stuff though.
This is a Great Show This was a fantastic show. Hottest Jack Straw ever...longest Franklin's on record and some solid jamming in Set 2.

good stuff  REVISED my 10th show and my first msg run. too bad there's an aweful hiss on this recording.

well someone changed it because there is no more hiss, but it still aint that great, sounds like they're in a box or something. not worth it in my opinion, even though I was there.

9-19-90 I agree with SteveCA that this show sounds a little flange'y, but it is also crispy as hell. Hornsby's vocals come thru crystal clear.....Phil's bass sounds excellent too. And what a second setlist...very well played

To OldSchoolJersey: I disagree that this is the hottest Jack Straw 'ever'. I would even suggest what I think is a better Hornsby era Jack Straw, that being 6-25-91 Sandstone. Additionally, I highly doubt that this show has the longest Franklin's ever. But everyone is perfectly entitled to their own opinion.

europe escape these shows were some of the fattest ever and about time the "dark star" came back out before they played it in Europe....there is no question about "Let It Grow" to lead into something that those of us who were there will never forget...

xoxo to whoever layed this down

Fun Show Saw this one (and the next) with my brother and a good friend..had a great time..my first MSG show.  one of my favorite GDTRFB's and Stella Blue's.  Great Let it Grow..nothing to dislike here.

Can't believe it's been 16 years since I saw this one =:-Q

Wrong File names The seeding for this show is wrong, in the second set.  I don't think there was a Playin' Reprise in this show.

Anyway wonderful sound.

solid show.... it is a bit erratic.  vocals were mic'd too loud to start, bruce comes in kind of off key in the start of jstraw but it was fixed by bertha.  the jack straw is nice, certainly not even close to the best on record (6-6-91 blows the face off this one).  but this is a fine show, the boys were tight, a fun set list.  wish they did half star ratings, this one isnt quite 4, more like 3.5, but im a glass half full guy.  so book it at 4.

ME AND MY UNCLE EVERYONE TALKS ABOUT THE JACK STRAW ON HERE IS IT THE BEST OR NOT? WELL I THINK THAT THE ME AND MY UNCLE ON HERE IS NO DOUBT THE BEST.  JERRY'S GIUTAR SOLO IS INSANE.  I WAS AT THIS SHOW AND I STILL HAVE DREAMS ABOUT IT OR MAYBE THEY ARE FLASHBACKS WHAT HAVE YOU.  THANK GOD FOR LUCY IN THE SKY WITH DIAMONDS OR I WOULD NEVER GET TO RE LIVE IT!!!

Jack Straw Jack Straw has an interesting evolution. I've seen it lead off and at the caboose of the first set. 
I need my Straw to be C R A C K L I N G with energy... Setting the tone for the show. Purely from a playing aspect... The notes are crisp and lyrics on que Veneta 72,  Cornell 77 and Chicago 2/1/78 is best. 
For energy.. Give me 7/24/87 when Bob couldn't get his rig right to start a long show with Dylan and Jerry goes to Tulsa in both his first and second verse... But that jam is pure ENERGY. 
give me Noblesville 90.. Or is it 91??? 

I like the Straw. Bertha. Uncle--> Big River. 
I like the combo JS--> Bertha. 
I also enjoy JS--> 1/2 Step. 

JS is a difficult song to mail right out of the chute. So difficult to get a good first song. JS is definitely my favorite starter. 

Second best is a good Cold Rain & Snow. 

If a lead off song is so crucial then the set that follows should benefit... Right? Most shows do benefit. 

I like how the 2/1/78 show starts. They picked up right where '77 left off. 

I also liked the versions Bob & Phil did in their recent tour.

For feeling like you were going to take off..7/24/87... Beautiful imperfection and all.

I love what I love, and I want it that way.. Best thing here is they stick with the historic end of the catalog 
with the exception of Memphis Blues and also fun Mighty Quinn. 
All tunes pretty much focus 1975 and the prime Hunter years
or just plain Old School GD covers.
At the time I didn't notice the major sound transition 
from Brent to Vince which is just as well.
but I am sure that had something to do with Bruce being so prevalent in the mix and me being ON THE BUS
 knocks on Hornsby?
 his singing with Garcia not always harmonious 
and also not a big fan of the accordion.
Otherwise Bruce is like a big time blood transfusion
for this rock and roll outfit. 
Ending Set One with H>S>F -- Garcia shreds!!!
 MSG was so amped for this run.
It felt to me like the 90's version of the Beatles at Shea
especially the last night of the run which was EPIC.
Just thinking what a stark contrast this was to the Ice Palace
where Without a Net suddenly became J-E-T ... L-A-G
Sweet Second Set😇
Who is on keyboard? Listening on the radio and had to sit in the car to hear the entire keyboard wildness. Amazing. Is this both Hornsby and Welnick? Really wild freeform jam.
